A **media query** applies styles conditionally based on device characteristics.
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) { ... }
```

CSS **animations** gradually change element styles using keyframes.
```css
@keyframes name { from { } to { } }
```

**@import** brings in external stylesheets or modules.
```css
@import url("styles.css");
```

```less
@variable-name: value;
```
Declares a Less variable that stores a value for reuse throughout the stylesheet. Variables can hold colors, dimensions, strings, or any CSS value and are evaluated lazily — meaning the last definition in scope wins. They enable centralized theming, consistent spacing scales, and easy global style changes.
